Due to platform ( the cloud where this systems run ) have ram reservation and stale 
proccesses still consume ram, every getCharacter() and other operations with big arrays/data
tasks has to be in a separate proccess (not worker) to be fire return and forget so it releases the ram alocation
for the proccess.

Am (the autorh) already working on a resolution in the workers service with a pub/sub patter for tasks eventualy the orchestrator
has to be "cold started" aswell cuz still manage the job for the workers we need a higher lvl spawner in the main thread,
it's purpose will be only to address if there's work and spawn the orchestrator, then the orchestrator will be managing the 
data/works/jobs to keep te main thread ram reserve free. 

Am already able to make the REST api aswell to use this new retrive from the worker characters pub/sub pattern so the project
(which does not include only these service/codebase/repo) is gonna prioritize this optimisation.
Please note the planned resolution will resolve in manny proccess spawns which is not best practice, but unfortunetlly
for this platform i dont see any other "native" resolution, i do it that way so we stay out of outside dependancies,
which if you are developer and read this u alredy know they are being exploited and this resolve in vonurabilities, am not
telling this approach is better and safer but is more controlled from me, which is my safespot.